    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prints made using the process of wood engraving, which is a relief process in which the design is cut into and printed from the grain end of a wood block; distinct from "woodcut (process)," which is a relief process using the plank side of a wood block.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
